2.3 (Mediator <-> Response) | Exposure

# Dx <- as.matrix(x)
# Dy <- as.matrix(y)
# Dz <- as.matrix(z)
# Pxz <- projection(Dx, Dz)  #U-center and compute projections
# Pyz <- projection(Dy, Dz)
# 
# x= mediator, data matrix or dist object of first sample
# y= response
# z= exposure
obs.pcoa = dudi.pco(cailliez(dM_jsd), scannf=F, nf=2)

#projection below:  This should remove the effect of aofib from dM_jsd.
proj_xz <- energy:::projection(as.matrix(dM_jsd), as.matrix(dist_aofib))
m1=proj_xz-min(proj_xz)+0.01
diag(m1)=0
# 
# str(proj_xz)
# apply(MARGIN = 2, X = proj_xz, FUN = function(x) sum(x^2))

obs.pcoa = dudi.pco(cailliez(as.dist(m1)), scannf=F, nf=2)
#obs.pcoa1 = dudi.pco(cailliez(as.dist(proj_xz)), scannf=F, nf=2)

3 Replicate Jun Chen publication

unifracs <- GUniFrac(otu.tab, tree.rooted)$unifracs
m.list <- list(BC=vegdist(otu.tab, method="bray"),
        JAC=as.matrix(vegdist(otu.tab, 'jaccard', binary=TRUE)),
        UniFrac=unifracs[, , c('d_UW')],
        GUniFrac=unifracs[, , c('d_0.5')],
        WUniFrac=unifracs[, , c('d_1')])

set.seed(12345)
MedTest_results <- MedOmniTest(aofib, bmi, m.list)
MedTest_results
## $margPs
## [1] 0.5568 0.0082 0.0901 0.5768 0.7859
## 
## $permP
## [1] 0.0309

Here we get the same p-value (0.0309) as in Jun Chen paper, so we can confirm that the data as well as the test have been accurately repeated. Note that only R version 3.5.3 results in 0.0309 p-value.

4.1 Source MODIMA

#source("~/Box Sync/mediation/modima/supplementary/modima_v2.R")
#devtools::load_all(path = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bashirhamidi/MODIMA/master/modima.R")

##

5.1 Slices

slices <- seq(0.01, 1, by = 0.01)
for(i in slices){
trees = treeSlice(tree.rooted, i)
print(trees)
for(tt in trees){
  ot = otu.tab[,tt$tip.label]
  print(dim(ot))
  if(any(rowSums(ot) == 0)){
    print("Samples with no taxa observed in the clade -- skip")
    next()
    }
  uni = GUniFrac(ot, tt)$unifracs
  m.l = list(BC=vegdist(ot, method="bray"),
              JAC=as.matrix(vegdist(ot, 'jaccard', binary=TRUE)),
              UniFrac=uni[, , c('d_UW')],
              GUniFrac=uni[, , c('d_0.5')],
              WUniFrac=uni[, , c('d_1')])
  MedTest_results = MedOmniTest(aofib, bmi, m.l)
  print(MedTest_results)
  }
}
